17. Rfc1 {does not work in the same way since after} Rc8 18. Rxc8 Qxc8 19. Rb5
b6 20. Rxd5 e6 $132 {Black gets decent counterplay.}) 13... Rc8 14. Nd2 Bxe2
15. Qxe2 e5 $1 {White is ready to push e3-e4, even by sacrificing the c3-pawn.
