in these positions and the analysis proves it} a6 (12... Kh8 13. Kb1 b6 14. Rg1
f4 15. Bf2 Ng8 16. Qe1 a5 17. Nc1 $14 {The position is very close, but I think
that White has more options to open the game at an appropriate moment.
Preparing b4-c5, in the long run, is an option, but also Black should be
