Bf1 f5 $132) 10... Nh5 11. g4 Qf6 (11... Nf4 {is still possible, but again
White is not forced to take immediately} 12. Qd2 h5 {looks like the only way
to keep some tension into the position.} 13. Bxf4 $1 exf4 14. gxh5 gxh5 15.
O-O-O {Black's dark square bishop is powerful, but the open "g" file is more
importang} Qf6 16. Rg1 Kh8 17. e5 $1 dxe5 18. Nc3 Qh6 19. c5 $40 {With an
overwhelming initiative}) 12. Nc3 Nf4 13. Qd2 h5 (13... c5 {is well met by} 14.
Ne2 b5 15. cxb5 h5 16. Nxf4 exf4 17. Bxf4 hxg4 18. O-O-O $16) 14. gxh5 $1 Nxh5
15. O-O-O {[%cal Re3g5]} Qe7 16. Bd3 Bd7 17. Rdg1 Kh7 18. Ne2 $40 {Black can't
keep the blockade on h5 any longer and White's initiative on the kingside
looks very dangerous. In the meantime, Black is not ready to organize any
severe threats on the other side of the board.}) 10. dxc6 bxc6 (10... Nxc6 {
Black keeps the material equal, but it is not in KID's spirit. The pawn on
