{is too slow and White is better after:} 17. Nf3 Re8 18. Kf1 Qa5 19. a4 Qb6 20.
Bg5 {[%cal Gf3h2]} Bg4 21. Ng1 Bc8 22. Rb1 Nb4 23. Qd2 Bf5 24. Rc1 {[%cal
Gc1c3,Gc3e3]}) 17. Qd2 Nb4 18. a4 Bf5 19. Nf3 Bb2 $1 {without analyzing this
position deeply it's simply impossible to find this and subsequent moves} (
19... Re8 20. Kf1 Be4 21. Ng5 $14) (19... Qc7 20. Kf1 Re8 21. Rc3 $1 $14) 20.
Kf1 Bxc1 21. Qxc1 (21. Qc3 $4 Bxh6 $19) 21... Na2 $1 22. Qf4 (22. Qb2 $4 Qc3
