Nxe2 Qxb3 $132) 23... Nxe2 24. Qf6 Qc3 25. Ne5 Ng3+ $3 {the last fantastic
resource just on the verge of mate! The main point is to close the way to
escape route of White's king} 26. fxg3 (26. Bxg3 Qc1+ 27. Ke2 Qc2+ $11) 26...
Qa1+ $1 (26... Qc1+ $4 27. Kf2 Qd2+ 28. Kg1 $18) 27. Ke2 (27. Kf2 Qd4+ $11 {
[%cal Gf2g1,Gg1h2]}) 27... Qb2+ 28. Ke3 Qd4+ 29. Kf3 Qc3+ $11 {Amazing line
and as many others in the modern chess ended in a draw.}) 14... Nd7 (14... Re8
{was tried in a correspondance game} 15. Rh4 (15. Rc1 $14 {leads to the
position which was analyzed after 14.Rc1}) 15... a5 {The game continues} 16.
Nf3 a4 17. Rb1 Nd7 18. Bd3 axb3 19. Rxb3 Qa5 20. a3 Ne5 21. Nxe5 Rxe5 22. Bf4
$14 {with a slight advantage for White 1/2  (30) Zordick,M (1984)-Geerken,L 
