16. Bd2 $1 {the strong maneuver. White transfers the bishop to the a1-h8
diagonal.} Nb4 17. Bc3 $14) 16. a3 $14 {This exchange sacrifice is very strong.
White restricted the a3-knight and is not afraid of Bxa1. He is planning to
continue with Ra2}) 15. Nf3 Re8 (15... Nf6 {after this, White manages to
achieve his desired setup} 16. Bd3 Re8 17. Rc1 $14 {Followed by Qd2, g3, etc...
}) 16. Rc1 (16. Bd3 {is possible too, but Black can hold the position after:}
